'''''Sengoku Ninja Tai''''' (Japanese: ''The Sengoku's Greatest Ninja'') is an [[arcade video game]] released by [[Data East]] in December 1980.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.arcade-history.com/?n=sengoku-ninja-tai-model-dt-102&page=detail&id=33101 | title=Sengoku Ninja Tai, DECO cass. By Data East (1980) }}</ref> Also known as '''''Ninja''''', ''Sengoku Ninja Tai'' was the second game released for the [[DECO Cassette System]], following ''Highway Chase'' also released in December 1980.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.arcade-history.com/?n=highway-chase-model-dt-101&page=detail&id=3870 | title=HWY Chase, DECO cass. By Data East (1980) }}</ref> The objective of the game is to shoot the [[ninja]]s before they reach the top of the castle.

